#PARKED - ROOT CAUSE SHARPENED (2026-06-11): two stacked parser facts kill
#every "if cond then choice name(X) ... target(Y)" bare ETB line:
#  1. the may/choice keyword check (MTGAbility.cpp ~2765) only matches at
#     POSITION 0 of sWithoutTc - inside an if-then it never fires;
#  2. the top-level tc extraction is not bracket-aware (round-23 family) and
#     steals the then-branch's target() before IfThenAbility recurses, so
#     even the sub-parse sees no chooser.
#@movedTo(this|myBattlefield) wrapping was tried and does NOT fire for cast
#ETBs (not an established idiom - Skyclave's is a death trigger).
#THE FAMILY IS HUGE: ~2600 primitive lines share the if-then+target( shape
#(choice-ETB damage/destroy/exile across the dataset) - this is a major
#engine round (if-then-choice family), not a Yannik data fix. Yannik also
#layers ability$! counter-assignment legs (one-strip-per-parse hazard) on
#the power>=1 buckets.
#DEEPER MAP (2026-06-11 second sitting, trace-proven): the parse/firing
#chain WORKS much further than thought - my earlier two-parser-facts note
#was WRONG about the then-branch losing its target() (the if-then parser
#recurses on the ORIGINAL string, MTGAbility.cpp ~2744, and the choice
#keyword matches at sub-parse position 0). Confirmed working: all bucket
#IfThenAbilitys fire at ETB, conds evaluate right, the bucket-2 May is
#addToGame'd, its menu spawns, choice 0 accepts, the GTA clone activates
#with a live current tc. THE ACTUAL KILL: one frame later ActionLayer::
#Update's cantCancel block auto-cancels the waiting action because
#ae->getActionTc()->validTargetsExist() returns FALSE - on that SAME tc
#pointer, canTarget(bears)=0, and BOTH legs fail (TargetZoneChooser zone
#check AND cd->match), though bears are a legal 'other creature[power=2]
#|mybattlefield' target. The mClone is NOT GC'd (trapped - never fires).
#Suspects: the clone-of-clone tc chain (ActionElement copy ctor clones tc
#per generation - DescriptorTargetChooser::clone + CardDescriptor copy may
#lose zone/descriptor state), or must-menu cantCancel semantics. NEXT:
#instrument DescriptorTargetChooser::clone fidelity (compare zones/nbzones/
#cd->types before vs after clone), or test with cantCancel forced 0.
#TRIED AND INSUFFICIENT (reverted, unproven): gating MayAbility::
#isReactingToTargetClick with the same validTargetsExist check Update uses
#(theory: the dead power-3 sibling joins the merged same-source menu and
#its empty chooser becomes the waiting action; canTarget(bears)=0 against
#power=3 fits the trace perfectly) - the probe still fails identically, so
#either entry routing differs or there is another layer. Next session:
